 {"id":"asupersync-pg9","title":"[Sync] Implement Cancel-Aware Mutex","description":"# Cancel-Aware Mutex

## Overview
Async mutex that integrates with cancellation protocol and tracks lock obligations.

## Core Type

```rust
use std::cell::UnsafeCell;
use std::ops::{Deref, DerefMut};

pub struct Mutex<T: ?Sized> {
    state: AtomicU32,
    waiters: WaiterQueue,
    data: UnsafeCell<T>,
}

// State bits:
// - Bit 0: locked
// - Bits 1-31: waiter count

impl<T> Mutex<T> {
    pub const fn new(value: T) -> Self {
        Self {
            state: AtomicU32::new(0),
            waiters: WaiterQueue::new(),
            data: UnsafeCell::new(value),
        }
    }

    pub fn into_inner(self) -> T {
        self.data.into_inner()
    }
}

impl<T: ?Sized> Mutex<T> {
    /// Acquire lock (cancel-aware)
    pub async fn lock(&self) -> MutexGuard<'_, T> {
        // Fast path: try_lock
        if let Some(guard) = self.try_lock() {
            return guard;
        }

        // Slow path: wait in queue
        self.lock_slow().await
    }

    /// Try to acquire lock immediately
    pub fn try_lock(&self) -> Option<MutexGuard<'_, T>> {
        let old = self.state.fetch_or(1, Ordering::Acquire);
        if old & 1 == 0 {
            Some(MutexGuard { mutex: self })
        } else {
            None
        }
    }

    async fn lock_slow(&self) -> MutexGuard<'_, T> {
        // Register waiter
        let waiter = Waiter::new();
        self.waiters.push(&waiter);

        loop {
            // Try to acquire
            if let Some(guard) = self.try_lock() {
                waiter.remove();
                return guard;
            }

            // Wait for notification or cancellation
            futures::select! {
                _ = waiter.notified() => continue,
                _ = cx.cancelled() => {
                    waiter.remove();
                    panic!("Mutex lock cancelled"); // Or return Result
                }
            }
        }
    }

    /// Get mutable reference (exclusive access guaranteed)
    pub fn get_mut(&mut self) -> &mut T {
        self.data.get_mut()
    }
}

unsafe impl<T: ?Sized + Send> Send for Mutex<T> {}
unsafe impl<T: ?Sized + Send> Sync for Mutex<T> {}
```

## MutexGuard

```rust
pub struct MutexGuard<'a, T: ?Sized> {
    mutex: &'a Mutex<T>,
}

impl<T: ?Sized> Deref for MutexGuard<'_, T> {
    type Target = T;
    fn deref(&self) -> &T {
        unsafe { &*self.mutex.data.get() }
    }
}

impl<T: ?Sized> DerefMut for MutexGuard<'_, T> {
    fn deref_mut(&mut self) -> &mut T {
        unsafe { &mut *self.mutex.data.get() }
    }
}

impl<T: ?Sized> Drop for MutexGuard<'_, T> {
    fn drop(&mut self) {
        // Unlock
        self.mutex.state.fetch_and(!1, Ordering::Release);
        // Wake one waiter
        self.mutex.waiters.wake_one();
    }
}
```

## OwnedMutexGuard

```rust
pub struct OwnedMutexGuard<T: ?Sized> {
    mutex: Arc<Mutex<T>>,
}

impl<T> Mutex<T> {
    /// Lock with owned guard (for 'static lifetime)
    pub async fn lock_owned(self: Arc<Self>) -> OwnedMutexGuard<T> {
        self.lock().await;
        OwnedMutexGuard { mutex: self }
    }
}
```

## Waiter Queue

```rust
struct WaiterQueue {
    head: AtomicPtr<Waiter>,
    tail: AtomicPtr<Waiter>,
}

struct Waiter {
    waker: AtomicWaker,
    next: AtomicPtr<Waiter>,
    queued: AtomicBool,
}

impl WaiterQueue {
    fn push(&self, waiter: &Waiter);
    fn wake_one(&self);
    fn wake_all(&self);
}
```

## Cancel-Safety
- Lock acquisition is cancel-safe (waiter removed on cancel)
- Guard drop always unlocks (no leak)
- Fairness: FIFO waiter queue

## Testing
- Basic lock/unlock
- Contention with multiple tasks
- Cancel during wait
- try_lock success/failure
- OwnedMutexGuard across await points
- No deadlock in single-threaded runtime

